- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper heavily relies on automata theory to prove theorems in combinatorics on words. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as combinatorics is a subfield of discrete mathematics. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper involves proving theorems using logical reasoning. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper involves analyzing the complexity of certain problems in combinatorics on words. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves manipulating automata, which can be seen as a data structure.
